OL,3,CD-Day 80 The Last Veterans: Harry
OL,4,CHoworth
OL,6,F"Fortunately for me, and I know he
OL,7,Fshouldn't of done it, and I wish I
OL,8,Fcould shake his hand, he pulled me out.
OL,10,F"I don't know who he is to this day. I
OL,11,Fhad loads and loads of bandoliers (a
OL,12,Fpocketed belt) and ammunition and just
OL,13,Fbefore I went they gave me a load more
OL,14,Fto put on as well.
OL,16,F"So if he hadn't have pulled me out I
OL,17,Fwas a goner. I couldn't have swum."
OL,19,FAs a Signaller, Mr Howorth was also
OL,20,Fweighed down by the wireless set he
OL,21,Fwas carrying.
