OL,3,CD-Day 80 The Last Veterans: Harry
OL,4,CHoworth
OL,6,F"We had commandeered an empty
OL,7,Fchateaux. It had an outside toilet and
OL,8,Fas I came out of the toilet door a
OL,9,FGerman aircraft flew over strafing and
OL,10,FI could hear the bullets hitting the
OL,11,Fground in front of me all the way
OL,12,Falong.
OL,14,F"And it got near me and it turned off.
OL,15,FIt did frighten you. After that it was
OL,16,Falright."
OL,18,F"You were just doing the job you had
OL,19,Fdone on exercises. It was a job that
OL,20,Fhad to be done. You are sorry about
OL,21,Fall those people who were killed."
